# Worker Task Packet

Use this document to hand one bounded subtask from the cloud orchestrator to the local worker.

The orchestrator creates or updates the packet's ledger entry when issuing this packet. The worker runs the 9-step test-first loop in `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md` and returns `docs/WORKER_RESULT_PACKET.md`.

## Header
- Packet ID:           `P-YYYY-MM-DD-NN`
- Date:
- Issued by:           cloud-orchestrator
- Spec ID:             `SPEC-NN-name` or `none`
- Target worker:       local-coder
- Priority:            LOW / MEDIUM / HIGH
- Packet Class:        FEATURE / BUGFIX / GREEN-SUITE / REFACTOR
- Packet Class Rationale: one line explaining why this class matches the change shape
- Concreteness Tier:   1 (exact files/tests/signatures) / 2 (sketch) / 3 (open-ended; discouraged)
- Max iterations:      FEATURE 3, BUGFIX 5, GREEN-SUITE 10, REFACTOR 3

